type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! kind

Lightweight schema engine for TiddlyWiki. Define each type's fields, constraints, title formula, and namespace memberships on a single tiddler. Spawn, edit, view, and validate typed instances through hand-rolled UIs with zero plugin dependencies.

!! Key features

* ''One tiddler per type'' — schema lives in fields and a JSON-encoded `kind.fields` array on a single tiddler; body stays free for prose documentation
* ''Namespaces'' — types declare `kind.namespaces` (multi-membership); a namespace switcher scopes what's visible
* ''Auto-computed titles'' — types declare a `kind.title-formula` filter; new instances get their title computed from sibling fields
* ''Live + bulk validation'' — inline errors as you edit, plus a wiki-wide validator report
* ''Typeahead refs'' — filterable text input + dropdown + selected pills with × remove; scales to large option sets
* ''Configurable stream-river view'' — each type chooses which fields appear in its in-river field bar; empty = bar hidden
* ''Instances Overview graph'' — open the ''[[Kind: Instances Overview]]'' tiddler for a whole-wiki graph of every instance, coloured per type, with toggleable per-ref-field edges and per-type show/hide; drag nodes to lay them out and positions persist. The hover tooltip offers per-node ''edit'' (live field editor in a modal), ''delete'' (confirm dialog; disabled with a hint while the node still has `parent`-field children) and ''Add child'' buttons for every kind whose `parent` field accepts the node's type — the create form opens with the parent pre-filled and the same validation as the Creator (needs a graph engine — see Prerequisites)
* ''Context preview'' — a cascade-palette side-preview (shown for any instance) that draws just the instance's neighbourhood in the parent-tree, reusing the Instances Overview layout/positions. Pills pick direction (''Descendants'' / ''Ancestors''), how many ''levels'' (1–5) to show, which ''edges'' to draw (multi-select), and which ''types'' to show (colour-coded chips — click to hide); all four persist globally. Edges are colour- and stroke-coded per relationship and labelled when more than one is shown (needs a graph engine + the bimlas kin-filter plugin — see Prerequisites)
* ''Hand-rolled UI'' — zero dependency on other rimir plugins (theme/components/typed)
* ''Cascade-palette integration'' — when `rimir/cascade-palette` ≥ 0.0.79 is installed, kind ships a bridge config (`kind.type` as the entity-type field) so any action declaring `ca-entity-type: <X>` automatically surfaces on Space against any tiddler with `kind.type: <X>` in any view. The four bundled instance-actions (Open, Edit fields, Edit kind schema, Delete) also carry `ca-applies: [<currentTiddler>has[kind.type]]`, so they show up on any kind-instance row regardless of its specific type

!! Prerequisites

No external prerequisites for the core schema/UI. Optional: `$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template` for the branded documentation hub; `$:/plugins/flibbles/graph` plus a rendering engine (`flibbles/vis-network` or `rimir/cytoscape-engine`) for the ''Instances Overview'' graph (it shows an install hint if absent). The ''Context'' side-preview additionally needs the `$:/plugins/bimlas/kin-filter` plugin (it walks the `parent` tree to a chosen depth).

!! Quick start

# Open the ''type-builder'' tab and define a new type (key, caption, icon, namespaces, title-formula, fields JSON).
# Open the ''creator'' tab, pick the type, fill the fields, click Create.
# Open the resulting tiddler in the story river — the stream-view field bar appears at the top.
# Use the ''validator'' tab for a wiki-wide constraint scan.
